+{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01DunrPGoKfzeCxLMjWCjdCM","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Implementation is complete. Here's a summary of what was built:\n\n**`src/index.ts`** - Versioned document store with:\n\n- **Document CRUD**: `create`, `get`, `update`, `delete` with deep cloning on all boundaries\n- **Version History**: Every `create`/`update` generates a versioned snapshot; `getHistory` returns chronological versions; `getVersion` retrieves specific versions\n- **Branching**: Default `main` branch, `createBranch` snapshots state (with optional `fromBranch`), `switchBranch` changes context, full isolation between branches\n- **Three-way Merge**: `merge(sourceBranch)` finds the common ancestor via fork points, compares both branches field-by-field:\n  - One-sided changes auto-resolve\n  - Same-value changes are conflict-free\n  - Different-value changes produce conflicts with dot-path notation\n  - Auto-applied when conflict-free; unchanged when conflicts exist\n  - `merged` field always shows ours-resolution preview\n\n**Key design decisions addressed in code review:**\n- Fork points updated after successful merges (prevents false conflicts on repeated merges)\n- Ancestry chain walking for grandchild/sibling branch topologies\n- Structural type change detection filters overlapping conflict paths\n- Version counter is per-instance, not module-level\n- Merge versions only created when content actually changes"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":448,"cache_read_input_tokens":77152,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":448},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8a8abe8a-01cb-4077-a42a-7211a72e5a8d","uuid":"7fdb8354-4f79-4a80-b1e7-8b71349b20a1"}
